      "content": "When a nation is suffering from high poverty, prioritizing debt reduction over immediate social needs is a morally and economically questionable choice. Investing in social safety nets acts as a powerful economic stimulus, putting money directly into the hands of consumers who will spend it, thereby boosting demand. A strong social foundation is the bedrock of a stable, functioning economy, and ignoring human suffering for the sake of abstract debt metrics is shortsighted.",
      "source": "target",
